If they are defined in the same python file you can give the type as a string However I would not recommend using the  ElnWithFormulaBaseSection  as it is being depricated But this is how you would do it:
 py
class CRCSample(CompositeSystem, EntryData):

    m_def = Section()

    sample_reference_from_collaboration = Quantity(
        type='CRCSample',
        description='If sample is received by collaboration, then reference it here.',
        a_eln={
            "component": "ReferenceEditQuantity"
        },
        shape=["*"],
    ) It's a bit hard for us to put in the deprecation warning but I think we need to improve there. It's listed under legacy sections in the python file but I fully understand that most people won't check that.

